WEBVTT

00:04.178 --> 00:04.352
.

00:04.395 --> 00:06.702
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:06.745 --> 00:08.443
sexually based offenses

00:08.486 --> 00:10.227
are considered
especially heinous.

00:10.271 --> 00:12.316
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:12.360 --> 00:14.144
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:14.188 --> 00:15.624
are members of an elite squad

00:15.667 --> 00:17.495
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:17.539 --> 00:19.019
These are their stories.

00:23.849 --> 00:25.242
- [gasps]
Oh, I am so sorry!

00:25.286 --> 00:26.722
- I'm so sorry.
- Oh, no, no.

00:26.765 --> 00:28.245
It's my fault.
I was trying to look at a map.

00:28.289 --> 00:29.551
I'm so sorry.

00:29.594 --> 00:31.553
- I'm local.
What are you looking for?

00:31.596 --> 00:34.469
- Oh, I, um, I...

00:34.512 --> 00:36.079
I just lost my friends.

00:36.123 --> 00:38.342
- They can't have gone far.

00:38.386 --> 00:40.562
Should we get into that pedicab
and go look for them?

00:42.346 --> 00:43.739
It could be fun.

00:43.782 --> 00:46.089
I'm Anais.

00:46.133 --> 00:48.265
- Um, I'm Meghan from Kansas.

00:48.309 --> 00:52.356
- Hello, ladies.
Your chariot awaits.

00:52.400 --> 00:54.663
[Jefferson Airplane's
"White Rabbit"]

00:54.706 --> 00:57.187
- Okay.

00:57.231 --> 00:59.276
This is so cool!

00:59.320 --> 01:01.670
- Uh, there's water back there
if you're thirsty.

01:01.713 --> 01:03.106
- Thank you.

01:03.150 --> 01:08.894
♪

01:08.938 --> 01:12.898
Oh, no, no.
My phone is dead.

01:12.942 --> 01:14.422
- I'm just a few blocks
from here.

01:14.465 --> 01:15.553
You could charge it
at my place.

01:15.597 --> 01:16.815
- No, no, no, no, no.

01:16.859 --> 01:19.731
[stuttering]
I don't want to put you out.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.168
- Change of plans.

01:21.211 --> 01:23.648
We're going
to the West Village.

01:23.692 --> 01:27.739
- ♪ And one pill
makes you small ♪

01:27.783 --> 01:32.570
- Depression and anxiety
are an organic response...

01:32.614 --> 01:36.183
[voice echoing]
To the stresses created by...

01:36.226 --> 01:38.359
our corrupt
and oppressive society.

01:38.402 --> 01:42.232
And how does the psychiatric
community respond?

01:42.276 --> 01:43.886
By numbing us,

01:43.929 --> 01:46.410
by treating the symptoms,

01:46.454 --> 01:51.328
and ignoring the root causes
of our alienation.

01:51.372 --> 01:53.591
- None of us are free.

01:53.635 --> 01:55.854
We're all cogs
in their machine.

01:57.987 --> 02:03.210
♪

02:03.253 --> 02:04.776
[machine whirring]

02:04.820 --> 02:09.303
- ♪ And if you go
chasing rabbits ♪

02:09.346 --> 02:13.568
♪ And you know
you're going to fall ♪

02:13.611 --> 02:17.354
♪ Tell 'em
a hookah-smoking caterpillar ♪

02:17.398 --> 02:19.617
- [breathing heavily]

02:19.661 --> 02:21.967
- ♪ Has given you the call

02:22.011 --> 02:23.578
[bird screeches]

02:23.621 --> 02:26.494
[whimpering]

02:26.537 --> 02:27.930
- ♪ When she was just small

02:27.973 --> 02:29.192
- Anais?

02:29.236 --> 02:31.325
Anais!

02:32.717 --> 02:34.763
[bird screeches]

02:34.806 --> 02:36.982
[ominous music]

02:37.026 --> 02:38.897
- I'm right here.

02:41.248 --> 02:43.250
[futuristic warbling]

02:43.293 --> 02:45.861
♪

02:45.904 --> 02:47.863
[ethereal whooshing]

02:47.906 --> 02:50.996
♪

02:51.040 --> 02:53.390
- ♪ When the men
on the chessboard ♪

02:53.434 --> 02:55.958
[voice modulating]
- Pay attention, Meghan.

02:56.001 --> 02:58.656
♪

02:58.700 --> 03:03.226
- ♪ And you just had
some kind of mushroom ♪

03:03.270 --> 03:04.880
♪ And your mind
is moving low ♪

03:04.923 --> 03:07.926
[bird screeches]

03:07.970 --> 03:10.886
- Why are you doing this?

03:10.929 --> 03:14.498
- You've spent your life
as one of the walking dead.

03:14.542 --> 03:18.241
- Climb out of your grave.
Find your true self.

03:18.285 --> 03:20.417
Live free.

03:20.461 --> 03:25.466
- ♪ Have fallen sloppy dead

03:25.509 --> 03:29.818
♪ And the White Knight
is talking backwards ♪

03:29.861 --> 03:33.604
♪ And the Red Queen's
off with her head ♪

03:33.648 --> 03:35.737
[bird screeches]

03:35.780 --> 03:37.826
♪ Remember

03:37.869 --> 03:42.787
♪ What the Dormouse said

03:42.831 --> 03:45.529
♪ Feed your head

03:45.573 --> 03:46.965
♪

03:47.009 --> 03:50.491
♪ Feed your head

03:52.667 --> 03:54.321
- [sobbing]
- Hey, hey.

03:54.364 --> 03:55.844
- [yells]
Help me!

03:55.887 --> 03:57.454
- Can you tell me your name?

03:57.498 --> 03:59.021
- Get the elves away
from me, please.

03:59.064 --> 04:00.762
- The elves? Elves?
- The machine elves!

04:00.805 --> 04:02.416
They want to take me
back there!

04:02.459 --> 04:03.678
- To where, honey?

04:03.721 --> 04:05.680
- To their world.

04:05.723 --> 04:08.726
[foreboding music]

04:08.770 --> 04:11.816
They told me, if I stay here,
I'm digging my own grave.

04:11.860 --> 04:13.731
- Okay, you know what?

04:13.775 --> 04:15.516
These folks right here,
they're good elves,

04:15.559 --> 04:17.822
and they're gonna help
take care of you, I promise.

04:17.866 --> 04:19.824
You're gonna be okay, honey.

04:19.868 --> 04:23.480
I need a tox screen
and a psych eval.

04:23.524 --> 04:24.742
- She give you anything?

04:24.786 --> 04:26.962
- She kept going on
about machine elves.

04:27.005 --> 04:28.442
- She's tripping out.
- Yeah.

04:28.485 --> 04:31.314
Drugs or a psychotic break
or both.

04:31.358 --> 04:33.664
- Sergeant,
I may have something.

04:33.708 --> 04:35.362
- On the way.

04:35.405 --> 04:38.365
♪

04:38.408 --> 04:40.323
- They tried to bury her alive.
- Or got her to do it.

04:40.367 --> 04:43.108
She mentioned
digging her own grave.

04:43.152 --> 04:45.720
- What the hell did they do
to this girl?

04:45.763 --> 04:50.942
♪

04:50.986 --> 04:53.945
[dramatic music]

04:53.989 --> 05:00.996
♪

05:39.817 --> 05:41.384
- Machine elves?

05:41.428 --> 05:42.733
- I'm having them check
for DMT.

05:42.777 --> 05:44.431
It's a common hallucination
among users.

05:44.474 --> 05:45.997
- And a very powerful
psychedelic.

05:46.041 --> 05:47.999
I-I haven't seen this in years.

05:48.043 --> 05:50.393
- She must've taken
a massive dose

05:50.437 --> 05:52.003
for her to still
be feeling symptoms.

05:52.047 --> 05:54.005
- So do we know
if she was assaulted?

05:54.049 --> 05:55.920
- She's got ligature marks,
she may be concussed.

05:55.964 --> 05:57.835
She's not lucid enough
to consent to a rape kit.

05:57.879 --> 05:59.576
- Okay, well, the chief
just called twice.

05:59.620 --> 06:02.013
So I need to find out
what we're looking at.

06:02.057 --> 06:05.669
- How is she?
Can we talk to her?

06:05.713 --> 06:08.977
- Uh, still having a lot
of terror and anxiety.

06:09.020 --> 06:11.066
We gave her diazepam
to calm her down,

06:11.109 --> 06:12.676
and we had to restrain her.

06:12.720 --> 06:16.027
We were afraid
that she would hurt herself.

06:16.071 --> 06:18.421
- Where am I?
It's so light in here.

06:18.465 --> 06:21.424
- You're at Mercy Hospital
in Manhattan.

06:21.468 --> 06:23.426
- New York?
I'm still here?

06:23.470 --> 06:24.688
- Yeah.

06:24.732 --> 06:25.907
- I want to go home.

06:25.950 --> 06:28.475
- Can you tell us
where your home is?

06:28.518 --> 06:31.434
- 190 Forest Avenue,
Great Bend, Kansas.

06:31.478 --> 06:33.175
My name is Meghan Gale.

06:33.218 --> 06:38.006
- Kat, I got a name
and address.

06:38.049 --> 06:39.834
- I'm on it.

06:39.877 --> 06:41.836
- It was dark.

06:41.879 --> 06:44.012
They held me down.
[sniffles]

06:44.055 --> 06:46.449
- Let's get these off her.

06:46.493 --> 06:48.495
Okay.

06:48.538 --> 06:51.498
Meghan, tell me about "they."

06:51.541 --> 06:53.456
- The machine elves.

06:53.500 --> 06:56.241
♪

06:56.285 --> 06:59.244
Before they came in,
the room spun,

06:59.288 --> 07:00.985
and then flowers bursting.

07:01.029 --> 07:03.684
♪

07:03.727 --> 07:05.512
And all the eyes...

07:05.555 --> 07:07.688
- The elves had eyes?

07:07.731 --> 07:09.907
- A hundred.

07:09.951 --> 07:13.215
Purple and yellow faces.

07:13.258 --> 07:16.740
Oh, and they crawled
all over me,

07:16.784 --> 07:18.002
inside me.

07:18.046 --> 07:21.528
- Inside you how?

07:21.571 --> 07:25.270
- Like they were having sex
with me.

07:25.314 --> 07:29.840
I tried to get away,
to get to my friends.

07:29.884 --> 07:31.494
- Thanks you, Mrs. Gale.

07:31.538 --> 07:33.235
Your daughter is safe
and in the hospital now.

07:33.278 --> 07:35.759
Once she can talk,
we'll have her give you a call.

07:35.803 --> 07:38.501
You're welcome.
Bye-bye.

07:38.545 --> 07:39.763
- What was she doing
in New York?

07:39.807 --> 07:41.504
- Bachelorette party.

07:41.548 --> 07:42.940
- And the other girls
didn't report her missing?

07:42.984 --> 07:44.986
- Yeah.
Some friends.

07:47.815 --> 07:49.207
- Oh, my God.

07:49.251 --> 07:50.818
Uh, we've been texting Meghan.
Is she okay?

07:50.861 --> 07:52.210
- Not really.

07:52.254 --> 07:54.038
When did you see her last?

07:54.082 --> 07:56.650
- Saturday night at--
at Fiddlesticks

07:56.693 --> 07:57.955
in Greenwich Village.

07:57.999 --> 08:00.175
- Were you girls
doing any drugs?

08:00.218 --> 08:02.003
- No, just fireball shots.

08:02.046 --> 08:03.961
Meghan wanted to call
her boyfriend,

08:04.005 --> 08:05.963
we went ahead,
she never showed up.

08:06.007 --> 08:08.662
- And you didn't think
to call the police?

08:08.705 --> 08:11.012
- We were here to party.

08:11.055 --> 08:13.797
It was our first time
in New York.

08:13.841 --> 08:17.018
- I saw a hawk above me.

08:17.061 --> 08:21.152
I tried to jump
on its back and fly away...

08:21.196 --> 08:23.328
but my hands melted
into the headboard.

08:23.372 --> 08:26.201
- So you were on a bed.

08:26.244 --> 08:28.986
- A woman brought me there.

08:29.030 --> 08:30.684
I thought she was helping me.

08:30.727 --> 08:32.163
- How was she helping you?

08:32.207 --> 08:34.688
- She got us a chariot,

08:34.731 --> 08:36.559
without a horse.

08:36.603 --> 08:38.082
- What about the driver?

08:38.126 --> 08:40.171
- He sat on a leopard.

08:40.215 --> 08:43.958
He was nice.
He gave me water.

08:44.001 --> 08:46.830
- Okay, Captain.

08:46.874 --> 08:48.789
Meghan's still not
making any sense.

08:48.832 --> 08:51.661
She said she got into some kind
of chariot with no horse.

08:51.705 --> 08:53.097
- Like this?

08:53.141 --> 08:55.186
- Pedicab
with leopard-print seats.

08:55.230 --> 08:57.232
That could be it.

08:57.275 --> 08:59.147
- Traffic cams caught 'em
up at Greenwich and 7th,

08:59.190 --> 09:00.931
and then lost them.

09:00.975 --> 09:03.020
And with the leopard-print
seats, we got an outlier.

09:03.064 --> 09:04.631
It might make him
easier to find.

09:04.674 --> 09:05.893
- Okay, send that still
to Rollins,

09:05.936 --> 09:07.372
and then we'll start walking.

09:07.416 --> 09:09.200
- Cool.
[horn honks distantly]

09:09.244 --> 09:12.943
- Yeah, that's her.
Anais.

09:12.987 --> 09:15.337
- Good, and--and she's the one
who hailed the pedicab?

09:15.380 --> 09:17.644
- Yeah, she told him
to take us to her place.

09:20.429 --> 09:23.171
There was an older man there.

09:23.214 --> 09:25.739
White beard,
he was like a wizard.

09:25.782 --> 09:29.220
[yawns]
He was teaching.

09:29.264 --> 09:32.267
- Teaching?
- He said...

09:32.310 --> 09:35.662
"Depression is the child
of repression."

09:35.705 --> 09:37.838
♪

09:37.881 --> 09:39.622
- Okay, Meghan,
are you getting tired?

09:39.666 --> 09:40.884
- No. No, no, no.

09:40.928 --> 09:42.059
I don't want
to fall back asleep.

09:42.103 --> 09:43.365
What if I go back there?

09:43.408 --> 09:44.975
I don't want to go
back to sleep.

09:45.019 --> 09:47.064
- It's okay. It's okay,
I'll--I'll stay with you.

09:47.108 --> 09:49.371
- Thank you.
[knock on door]

09:49.414 --> 09:52.635
- Captain,
do you have a second?

09:52.679 --> 09:54.071
- Excuse me.

09:54.115 --> 09:55.638
- Okay, well,
your detective was right.

09:55.682 --> 09:56.900
There's a reason
Meghan was so out of it.

09:56.944 --> 09:58.162
- Well, DMT.
- Yeah.

09:58.206 --> 10:00.774
Lab says a hundred times
the usual dose.

10:00.817 --> 10:02.340
Also traces of ketamine.

10:02.384 --> 10:03.733
- Anything else?

10:03.777 --> 10:05.300
- Well, if I had to guess, GHB.

10:05.343 --> 10:08.869
- So too long ago
to show on a tox screen.

10:08.912 --> 10:10.218
Thank you.
- Okay.

10:10.261 --> 10:11.959
One more thing.

10:12.002 --> 10:15.092
DMT overdose is not
a regular Saturday night,

10:15.136 --> 10:16.877
so I called
a Bellevue nurse I know

10:16.920 --> 10:18.139
to see if they had any cases.

10:18.182 --> 10:19.967
She said a girl was brought in

10:20.010 --> 10:22.360
two weeks ago,
same tox screen.

10:22.404 --> 10:24.711
- Where can we find her?
- She's still there.

10:24.754 --> 10:28.018
Psych ward.
Never came back.

10:28.062 --> 10:30.412
♪

10:30.455 --> 10:32.632
- Thank you.

10:38.855 --> 10:39.247
.

10:39.290 --> 10:42.424
- Two victims dosed with DMT?
- Meghan Gale and Jane Doe.

10:42.467 --> 10:45.819
She was found two weeks ago,
6:00 a.m., wandering,

10:45.862 --> 10:49.344
wearing a sheet by the fountain
at Rockefeller Center.

10:49.387 --> 10:51.085
- How did we miss it?

10:51.128 --> 10:54.175
- The unis thought
that she was homeless, an EDP.

10:54.218 --> 10:56.177
So they took her
to the psych ward.

10:56.220 --> 10:59.833
She hasn't uttered
a coherent sentence since.

10:59.876 --> 11:03.488
Doctor says that she stays
awake for days at a time.

11:03.532 --> 11:05.099
She might be afraid to sleep.

11:05.142 --> 11:07.101
- We have no idea who she is?
- Oh, no.

11:07.144 --> 11:10.757
There's no ID, there's no DNA,
there's no missing persons.

11:10.800 --> 11:12.846
Now, the medical report shows
signs of sexual assault,

11:12.889 --> 11:14.412
and from the tox screen,

11:14.456 --> 11:16.240
she was taking
prescription antipsychotics.

11:16.284 --> 11:18.373
- What are we looking at here?

11:18.416 --> 11:20.114
- It's a man-woman team

11:20.157 --> 11:23.421
who pick very young victims,

11:23.465 --> 11:26.381
take them to some group house,

11:26.424 --> 11:29.689
drug them with DMT, rape them,
and then--and then dump them

11:29.732 --> 11:32.300
in some public space.

11:32.343 --> 11:34.215
- Have you ever seen
something like this before?

11:34.258 --> 11:36.260
Could it be some kind of cult?
- I don't know.

11:36.304 --> 11:39.481
I mean, Meghan says
that she remembers an older man

11:39.524 --> 11:41.570
talking to the group.

11:41.613 --> 11:44.529
She called him a wizard.

11:44.573 --> 11:45.617
[cell phone chirps, vibrates]

11:45.661 --> 11:47.358
- Until we have more answers,

11:47.402 --> 11:50.231
let's try and keep the details
out of the press.

11:50.274 --> 11:53.364
- Well, we may not be able to.

11:53.408 --> 11:54.757
Another victim just turned up.

11:54.801 --> 11:56.367
[forlorn music]

11:56.411 --> 11:58.761
Central Park, off 5th Avenue.

11:58.805 --> 12:01.155
♪

12:01.198 --> 12:02.591
- We got a 911 call.

12:02.634 --> 12:04.288
Screaming woman
dumped out of a pedicab.

12:04.332 --> 12:05.725
- They get a look
at the driver?

12:05.768 --> 12:08.728
- Not really.
Said he had on a top hat.

12:08.771 --> 12:11.818
We get here, she's blindfolded,
hands tied, nothing on her.

12:11.861 --> 12:14.908
- She say anything?
- Some language I never heard.

12:14.951 --> 12:17.388
- [grunting forcefully]

12:17.432 --> 12:19.260
- Hey, it's okay.
It's okay, honey.

12:19.303 --> 12:20.783
We're gonna take care
of you, okay?

12:20.827 --> 12:22.437
- [yells]

12:22.480 --> 12:25.483
[screaming Swedish]

12:27.703 --> 12:29.444
- Yes, Chief,
she's an exchange student

12:29.487 --> 12:30.532
from Sweden.

12:30.575 --> 12:32.534
Her name is Freja Bergdahl.

12:32.577 --> 12:35.232
This one went missing
two days ago.

12:35.276 --> 12:37.278
You know, the roommate says
that she's a good kid,

12:37.321 --> 12:40.803
she's a grad student at Pratt,
not a drug taker.

12:40.847 --> 12:45.547
- The trolls kept me
in the dark.

12:45.590 --> 12:47.767
They held me down.

12:47.810 --> 12:51.466
They were inside me.

12:51.509 --> 12:52.859
- Was anyone with the trolls?

12:55.252 --> 12:56.645
- A king.

12:56.688 --> 13:00.823
W-with a white beard.

13:00.867 --> 13:03.695
Like a John Bauer fairy tale.

13:03.739 --> 13:05.523
He ruled the house.

13:05.567 --> 13:07.482
- Tell me about the house.

13:07.525 --> 13:08.875
H-how did you get there?

13:10.224 --> 13:12.574
- It was bumpy.

13:12.617 --> 13:14.663
- You were in a car?

13:14.706 --> 13:17.405
- Nej.
A bicycle.

13:17.448 --> 13:19.842
- Okay.
Good, Freja.

13:19.886 --> 13:21.539
Do you remember--
you remember seeing

13:21.583 --> 13:22.889
anything else?

13:26.414 --> 13:31.854
- We went past
a giant stone woman.

13:31.898 --> 13:34.378
And later,

13:34.422 --> 13:35.945
up a high stoop.

13:37.468 --> 13:39.296
Many stairs.

13:39.340 --> 13:41.995
- Freja, you're an art student.

13:42.038 --> 13:44.432
All right, you think
you can draw the--

13:44.475 --> 13:48.653
the woman and the trolls?

13:48.697 --> 13:51.395
- Machine elves,
Swedish trolls?

13:51.439 --> 13:52.962
So this girl was
also drugged with DMT?

13:53.006 --> 13:54.877
- A huge dose, and ketamine.

13:54.921 --> 13:57.271
- Both rape kits came back with
semen from multiple donors.

13:57.314 --> 13:58.489
No hits.

13:58.533 --> 14:00.274
- No criminal records,
not DNA savvy.

14:00.317 --> 14:02.493
Led by a wizard?
A king?

14:02.537 --> 14:04.669
- Yeah, who has
unlimited access to DMT,

14:04.713 --> 14:06.236
tougher to get
than cocaine and meth.

14:06.280 --> 14:07.803
- You know,
shamans in South America

14:07.847 --> 14:10.675
use it to access
a higher dimension.

14:10.719 --> 14:13.374
- So our wizard gets DMT
through a religious group

14:13.417 --> 14:14.810
or medical research?

14:14.854 --> 14:16.377
- We're checking
clinical trials

14:16.420 --> 14:18.248
to see if they've had
any of the drugs stolen.

14:18.292 --> 14:20.033
- Anything else to go on?

14:20.076 --> 14:22.470
- Freja remembered passing

14:22.513 --> 14:24.864
a huge stone woman.

14:24.907 --> 14:27.040
Maybe a hallucination.

14:27.083 --> 14:28.519
- Or not.

14:28.563 --> 14:30.391
What about
the Bust of Sylvette?

14:31.958 --> 14:34.525
The Picasso statue.
- By the I.M. Pei Towers.

14:34.569 --> 14:36.266
Okay, we'll start a canvass.

14:36.310 --> 14:38.529
- Why don't you put Freja
in a car, drive her around,

14:38.573 --> 14:39.748
see what comes back?

14:39.791 --> 14:41.402
- Um, uh, she's...

14:41.445 --> 14:43.404
she's actually
quite traumatized.

14:43.447 --> 14:44.927
- I won't tell you
how to do your job, Captain.

14:44.971 --> 14:46.929
- Thank you.

14:46.973 --> 14:48.757
- But I know you'll be
sensitive to her experience,

14:48.800 --> 14:49.801
and to our needs.

14:52.979 --> 14:54.937
We need a break.

14:54.981 --> 14:58.723
[chilling music]

14:58.767 --> 15:00.900
- There she is.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.945
♪

15:02.989 --> 15:04.773
- The giant stone woman.

15:04.816 --> 15:06.949
- Yes.

15:06.993 --> 15:08.733
Yes.

15:08.777 --> 15:10.866
We were here.

15:10.910 --> 15:12.302
- Okay.

15:13.651 --> 15:14.914
Okay.

15:16.350 --> 15:18.482
♪

15:18.526 --> 15:22.530
So Freja, is there anything
else that you remember passing?

15:22.573 --> 15:27.578
♪

15:27.622 --> 15:29.624
On the side of the road,

15:29.667 --> 15:34.324
a canopy of floating triangles.

15:34.368 --> 15:35.717
♪

15:35.760 --> 15:36.979
- Okay.

15:38.589 --> 15:42.985
♪

15:43.029 --> 15:44.900
- There!

15:44.944 --> 15:46.728
Those triangles.

15:46.771 --> 15:48.948
♪

15:48.991 --> 15:50.906
- That's the AIDS Memorial.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.516
- We are close.

15:52.560 --> 15:57.521
♪

15:57.565 --> 15:59.654
That green wall
with the posters?

15:59.697 --> 16:01.351
Turn here.

16:14.712 --> 16:17.019
♪

16:17.063 --> 16:19.674
It was dark and...
- Okay.

16:19.717 --> 16:22.372
You said that the house
had a high stoop.

16:22.416 --> 16:23.547
- Mm-hmm.

16:25.549 --> 16:28.639
Oh, uh,
I don't want to do this.

16:28.683 --> 16:30.554
- Freja, was it one of these?

16:30.598 --> 16:32.600
- With the red door.
- Okay.

16:32.643 --> 16:34.123
- I have to go.

16:34.167 --> 16:35.864
- Listen to me.
Listen to me, we're done.

16:35.907 --> 16:37.039
We're done.
We're done.

16:37.083 --> 16:38.562
It's over, and you're safe.

16:38.606 --> 16:40.086
You're safe, okay?

16:40.129 --> 16:42.871
You're safe.
- [sobbing]

16:50.879 --> 16:51.053
.

16:51.097 --> 16:53.316
- So the brownstone here
with the red door was bought

16:53.360 --> 16:55.057
30 years ago by a foundation

16:55.101 --> 16:56.493
for radical therapy,

16:56.537 --> 16:59.279
and gifted to Julius Adler
for his institute.

16:59.322 --> 17:00.584
- He's
the white-bearded wizard?

17:00.628 --> 17:02.369
- Dr. Julius Adler,

17:02.412 --> 17:04.371
an esteemed professor
of Radical Psychiatry

17:04.414 --> 17:07.548
at Tompkins Square,
a prolific author, and--

17:07.591 --> 17:09.419
- And a freak.

17:09.463 --> 17:11.639
He uses psychedelics
as a cure-all.

17:11.682 --> 17:14.250
- In controlled,
clinical studies.

17:14.294 --> 17:17.210
- I ran the building.
It's got nonprofit status.

17:17.253 --> 17:19.386
Seven complaints
over the last year.

17:19.429 --> 17:20.996
Noise, kids partying,

17:21.040 --> 17:23.216
a cello being thrown out
of a third-story window.

17:23.259 --> 17:25.131
- And both victims remember
going into that brownstone?

17:25.174 --> 17:26.567
Can they ID him?

17:26.610 --> 17:29.309
- No, but Freja
was clearly triggered.

17:29.352 --> 17:32.399
Now, she thinks
she remembers the red door

17:32.442 --> 17:34.053
and the high stoop.

17:34.096 --> 17:36.925
- She thinks.
She also remembered trolls.

17:36.968 --> 17:38.622
- There's reason to believe
he has DMT

17:38.666 --> 17:40.146
and other psychedelics inside.

17:40.189 --> 17:41.495
- But if he's running
clinical trials,

17:41.538 --> 17:43.018
that may not be illegal.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.193
- Come on, Carisi,
you can trust us.

17:44.237 --> 17:45.499
- I do, Fin, but every time

17:45.542 --> 17:46.543
I go out on a limb
for you guys,

17:46.587 --> 17:48.067
somebody saws it off.

17:48.110 --> 17:49.546
Look,
it's an academic institute.

17:49.590 --> 17:51.331
I need some patina
of probable cause.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.508
- Patina?

17:54.551 --> 17:56.205
- That guy was really a cop?

17:56.249 --> 17:58.425
- Hey, guys, he's just--
he's just doing his job.

17:58.468 --> 18:00.166
- We could take a run at Adler,

18:00.209 --> 18:01.167
see if he gives us anything.

18:01.210 --> 18:02.951
- That's a good idea.

18:02.994 --> 18:06.041
- Kat, Fin,
you're off to see the wizard.

18:06.085 --> 18:06.868
- Okay.

18:10.741 --> 18:13.527
[door bell buzzes]

18:13.570 --> 18:14.702
- What's our play?

18:14.745 --> 18:16.007
- Well, he's a shrink,

18:16.051 --> 18:17.226
so he's gonna try to read us.

18:17.270 --> 18:20.534
So suss him out, let him talk.

18:20.577 --> 18:22.579
- Yes?
- NYPD.

18:22.623 --> 18:24.407
Are you Julius Adler?

18:24.451 --> 18:25.408
- Yes, I am.

18:25.452 --> 18:27.932
Is this about the cello?

18:27.976 --> 18:29.543
- Actually, it's about
the kidnapping

18:29.586 --> 18:30.979
of three young women.

18:31.022 --> 18:33.068
- Oh, that's horrible.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.201
- We think they may
have been brought here.

18:35.244 --> 18:36.985
- You recognize
any of these women?

18:38.204 --> 18:39.988
[foreboding music]

18:40.031 --> 18:42.164
- Uh, no.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.079
♪

18:44.123 --> 18:45.559
No, no.

18:45.602 --> 18:48.953
But we have so many,
uh, students and teachers,

18:48.997 --> 18:50.390
patients coming in and out.

18:50.433 --> 18:54.263
They could've audited a class
or an open house.

18:54.307 --> 18:56.135
- Actually, I don't really
think that's it.

18:56.178 --> 18:59.094
They said that they were raped
and drugged here.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.575
- Really?
Tell me about that.

19:01.618 --> 19:03.968
W-what exactly did they say?

19:04.012 --> 19:05.448
- That's confidential.

19:05.492 --> 19:07.233
- Oh.

19:07.276 --> 19:09.104
Well, I'm a good therapist,

19:09.148 --> 19:13.195
but even I can't explain
behavior you won't describe.

19:13.239 --> 19:16.198
- Well, I can tell you
that they were terrified.

19:16.242 --> 19:17.765
♪

19:17.808 --> 19:22.117
- The work that we do here,
uh, pushes boundaries.

19:22.161 --> 19:25.120
Is it possible that while
they were in process, uh,

19:25.164 --> 19:27.340
feelings of helplessness
emerged

19:27.383 --> 19:30.256
or traumatic memories
resurfaced?

19:30.299 --> 19:32.083
- Maybe.

19:32.127 --> 19:33.998
Why don't we come inside
and you could show us

19:34.042 --> 19:35.174
where these memories surfaced?

19:35.217 --> 19:36.436
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:36.479 --> 19:38.133
I'm assuming
you don't have a warrant?

19:38.177 --> 19:41.571
Uh, like you, I have to
respect confidentiality.

19:41.615 --> 19:45.009
I hope
that this was productive.

19:49.449 --> 19:51.451
- I heard Adler wasn't helpful.

19:51.494 --> 19:53.453
- Nope.

19:53.496 --> 19:56.020
But he did claim that so many
students passed through

19:56.064 --> 19:58.501
the doors of his institute that
he can't keep track of them.

19:58.545 --> 20:01.330
- I, um, didn't want
to get into it before,

20:01.374 --> 20:02.636
but back in Atlanta,

20:02.679 --> 20:04.159
when I was going through
some stuff,

20:04.203 --> 20:05.160
I took some psych courses

20:05.204 --> 20:06.422
at Georgia State,

20:06.466 --> 20:09.295
and Adler
was a guest professor.

20:09.338 --> 20:12.080
I'm telling you, this man...

20:12.123 --> 20:16.215
he's brilliant, empathically,
a real healer.

20:16.258 --> 20:18.042
Whatever happened
to those girls,

20:18.086 --> 20:19.566
I can't imagine
how he'd be involved.

20:19.609 --> 20:22.830
- Rollins, I hear you.

20:22.873 --> 20:26.268
But you and I both know
that that was a long time ago,

20:26.312 --> 20:27.269
and people change.

20:27.313 --> 20:29.445
- They do.

20:29.489 --> 20:32.231
But it sounds like
he still keeps

20:32.274 --> 20:33.580
an open door for his students.

20:33.623 --> 20:37.279
It couldn't hurt
to make an approach.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.502
[dramatic musical sting]

20:42.545 --> 20:45.244
- Psychiatry has devolved

20:45.287 --> 20:49.073
into social control.

20:49.117 --> 20:53.295
Depression, anxiety are not
symptoms of mental illness.

20:53.339 --> 20:55.123
They are, in truth,

20:55.166 --> 20:58.387
an organic reaction
to oppression.

20:58.431 --> 21:02.217
Sexual repression,
economic disparity,

21:02.261 --> 21:07.396
misogyny, racism,
these are all part of the root.

21:07.440 --> 21:10.704
And now, as psychiatrists
are fond of saying,

21:10.747 --> 21:13.446
I think this is
a good place to stop.

21:13.489 --> 21:15.317
I'll see you all next week.

21:18.189 --> 21:21.367
- Hi, Dr. Adler.
- Yes?

21:21.410 --> 21:23.238
- I'm a big admirer of yours.

21:23.282 --> 21:24.718
- Oh.
- Amanda.

21:24.761 --> 21:27.503
I actually took a lecture class
of yours years ago.

21:27.547 --> 21:30.593
- Yeah, yes,
in, uh, Atlanta, right?

21:30.637 --> 21:32.726
- That's right.
- Yeah.

21:32.769 --> 21:34.597
Well, aren't you a fish
out of water.

21:34.641 --> 21:36.338
- I-I am.

21:36.382 --> 21:38.427
Guess you could say I was
searching for a bigger pond.

21:38.471 --> 21:39.907
- Hmm.
- [chuckles]

21:39.950 --> 21:42.257
Um, I'm finishing up
my master's

21:42.301 --> 21:43.737
in liberation psychiatry,

21:43.780 --> 21:46.130
and all roads
still lead to you.

21:46.174 --> 21:48.219
- Oh, call me Rome.

21:48.263 --> 21:52.354
- And your book, "Oppression,
Repression, Depression,"

21:52.398 --> 21:54.400
it really resonated with me.

21:54.443 --> 21:57.533
- Ah, so you're the one
who bought it.

21:57.577 --> 22:00.667
- Why, are you surprised
your books aren't best sellers?

22:00.710 --> 22:03.278
Pharmaceutical companies,
mainstream psychiatry,

22:03.322 --> 22:04.888
they don't want
the truth to get out.

22:04.932 --> 22:07.369
- Dad, there's a lot of people
that are waiting for you.

22:07.413 --> 22:09.502
- Oh.
- Oh, I'm--I'm sorry.

22:09.545 --> 22:11.678
Just, um, thanks.

22:11.721 --> 22:12.679
- Yes.
- Thanks.

22:12.722 --> 22:14.376
- Yeah. Amanda?

22:14.420 --> 22:16.639
Um, I don't know
if you're busy later tonight,

22:16.683 --> 22:20.643
but, uh, I'm having
an open house study session.

22:20.687 --> 22:23.690
You're more than welcome
to join us.

22:23.733 --> 22:25.300
♪

22:25.344 --> 22:29.348
- Yeah.
[chuckles]

22:29.391 --> 22:35.615
♪

22:35.658 --> 22:38.226
- And what about you, Amanda?

22:38.269 --> 22:40.968
Do you feel alienated
from your true self?

22:41.011 --> 22:43.666
- I do a lot of the times.
- Well, we all do.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.451
- How long are we gonna let
this guy hit on Rollins?

22:45.494 --> 22:47.409
- We're gonna wait
for probable cause.

22:47.453 --> 22:49.193
- Or machine elves?

22:49.237 --> 22:50.543
Sorry.

22:50.586 --> 22:51.979
I don't believe
in regular psychiatry,

22:52.022 --> 22:52.980
let alone this.

22:53.023 --> 22:54.373
- I'm with Kat.

22:54.416 --> 22:55.809
Paying someone
to listen to you talk?

22:55.852 --> 22:58.333
- Guys, please.
- Amanda...

22:58.377 --> 23:01.815
our society so suffocates
the human soul,

23:01.858 --> 23:04.687
our distance from true self
so profound,

23:04.731 --> 23:08.865
that we turn to liquor,
uh, to gambling...

23:08.909 --> 23:12.434
- Casual sex that just
reinforces our low self-esteem.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.654
- But nothing seems
to fill the void.

23:14.697 --> 23:15.829
- Yes.

23:15.872 --> 23:17.657
Amanda,

23:17.700 --> 23:20.007
the reality that you're
experiencing right now

23:20.050 --> 23:22.444
is not the only reality,

23:22.488 --> 23:24.359
but we're all so programmed,

23:24.403 --> 23:27.667
that we, uh, we can't even
access the pathways

23:27.710 --> 23:29.886
in our own brains.

23:29.930 --> 23:31.758
Oh, here we go.

23:31.801 --> 23:33.412
- What's up with that van?
- You know...

23:33.455 --> 23:35.631
primitive cultures
understood this.

23:35.675 --> 23:37.764
They had a life
built around ritual...

23:37.807 --> 23:38.982
- White male.

23:39.026 --> 23:40.549
- Look like our pedicab driver?

23:40.593 --> 23:42.377
- To allow them
to enter a dream state.

23:42.421 --> 23:43.857
Amanda...

23:43.900 --> 23:46.555
- Industrial tanks.

23:46.599 --> 23:48.688
Maybe ether?
- I knew it.

23:48.731 --> 23:50.690
They're cooking
their own drugs.

23:50.733 --> 23:52.300
- [sighs]

23:52.343 --> 23:54.868
- And you can
experience it too.

23:54.911 --> 23:59.438
♪

23:59.481 --> 24:02.266
- I'm not sure
that's such a good idea.

24:02.310 --> 24:04.399
- Amanda.

24:04.443 --> 24:07.750
Don't be afraid
to swim past the breakers.

24:09.535 --> 24:14.583
♪

24:17.107 --> 24:18.935
- We lost visual.
Let's move.

24:21.024 --> 24:22.852
- Fin!

24:22.896 --> 24:24.375
- Put your hands
where I can see 'em!

24:24.419 --> 24:25.899
Get 'em up!
- This is all legal.

24:25.942 --> 24:27.901
♪

24:27.944 --> 24:30.033
- NYPD!

24:30.077 --> 24:31.905
Drugs down.
Hands up.

24:31.948 --> 24:33.689
- This is an academic seminar.

24:33.733 --> 24:35.343
We have a right
to freedom of inquiry here.

24:35.386 --> 24:36.779
- You have a right
to remain silent.

24:36.823 --> 24:39.086
Anything you say can
and will be used against you.

24:39.129 --> 24:40.914
- Dad?
- It's okay, hon.

24:40.957 --> 24:42.916
It's okay.
- Rollins, are you okay?

24:42.959 --> 24:45.701
- Yeah, I didn't inhale.
- Are you sure?

24:45.745 --> 24:48.399
- Wait, you're a cop?

24:48.443 --> 24:49.575
- Captain, everyone goes?

24:49.618 --> 24:51.315
- Everyone goes
until we find out

24:51.359 --> 24:52.752
who's a vic and who's a perp.

24:52.795 --> 24:55.581
Let's go, gentlemen.
Stand up, please.

24:55.624 --> 24:57.104
Stand up.
On your feet.

24:57.147 --> 24:58.975
Nice and easy.
Nice and easy.

24:59.019 --> 25:00.411
Hands up.

25:00.455 --> 25:03.806
[ominous music]

25:03.850 --> 25:09.377
♪

25:09.420 --> 25:12.467
- Meghan's hawk.

25:12.511 --> 25:14.687
♪

25:14.730 --> 25:15.992
- Rollins.

25:17.994 --> 25:22.477
♪

25:22.521 --> 25:23.957
Rollins.
- Hmm?

25:24.000 --> 25:25.349
- Hey.

25:30.529 --> 25:30.877
.

25:30.920 --> 25:35.098
- So, where, uh,
did you go, Amanda?

25:35.142 --> 25:36.839
- Excuse me?

25:36.883 --> 25:40.364
- Well, I saw the light
come on in your eyes,

25:40.408 --> 25:42.758
your soul leave its cage.

25:42.802 --> 25:45.369
You were on your journey.

25:45.413 --> 25:48.459
So I'm curious,

25:48.503 --> 25:50.113
where did you go?

25:53.900 --> 25:55.815
- What the hell is he doing?

25:55.858 --> 25:57.947
- She's just letting him
establish rapport.

25:57.991 --> 25:59.862
- Uh-huh.

25:59.906 --> 26:01.560
Who else did we pick up?

26:01.603 --> 26:03.779
- We're a family.

26:03.823 --> 26:05.128
Maybe not the Brady Bunch,

26:05.172 --> 26:07.522
but that was
an artificial construct

26:07.566 --> 26:09.045
to make us all conform.

26:09.089 --> 26:10.307
- Your father tell you that?

26:10.351 --> 26:12.179
- And more.

26:12.222 --> 26:16.052
Every day since I was three,
when my mother died.

26:16.096 --> 26:20.274
He sacrificed everything
to take care of me.

26:20.317 --> 26:23.364
What he's built and taught.

26:23.407 --> 26:24.887
No one can take that away.

26:24.931 --> 26:27.237
- Which is what, exactly?

26:28.935 --> 26:31.154
- How to be whole.

26:31.198 --> 26:35.855
People come to him searching
for an alternative path.

26:35.898 --> 26:37.900
- So she's drunk
the Kool-Aid too.

26:37.944 --> 26:39.075
Do we have anybody else?

26:39.119 --> 26:40.903
- Caleb, the pedicab driver,

26:40.947 --> 26:44.037
and ten others
who are all on video

26:44.080 --> 26:45.821
taking a hit from the pipe.

26:45.865 --> 26:47.606
- Adler swears
there were no assaults.

26:47.649 --> 26:49.390
- No surprise there.
What do the victims say?

26:49.433 --> 26:52.262
- Uh, victim.
Freja went back to Stockholm.

26:52.306 --> 26:55.788
So Meghan ID'd Anais and Caleb,

26:55.831 --> 26:58.486
and she remembers Adler
giving a lecture.

26:58.529 --> 27:01.315
- But after that,
machine elves.

27:01.358 --> 27:03.099
We got any DNA hits
from the men?

27:03.143 --> 27:05.406
- Not yet,
but they're in front of it.

27:05.449 --> 27:07.930
- They claim it was
a mutual psychonautic

27:07.974 --> 27:09.976
sexual exploration.

27:10.019 --> 27:12.282
- Translation, consensual?
- Yeah.

27:12.326 --> 27:16.591
- Okay, so this guy claims
academic freedom,

27:16.635 --> 27:18.158
but the truth is,
he's a puppet master

27:18.201 --> 27:19.899
who gets his acolytes
to rape and torture girls.

27:19.942 --> 27:21.030
- I don't think
that's what this is.

27:21.074 --> 27:22.292
- Oh, yeah?

27:22.336 --> 27:23.859
So Meghan wanted
to dig her own grave,

27:23.903 --> 27:25.426
run around half-naked
in a bed sheet?

27:27.515 --> 27:29.038
- Caleb's parents are here.

27:34.478 --> 27:38.091
- We drove down from Syracuse
as soon as we heard.

27:38.134 --> 27:40.180
Caleb, he's--
he's had his problems.

27:40.223 --> 27:43.226
- Oh, with depression,
self-harm.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.489
Caleb's not even
taking classes anymore.

27:45.533 --> 27:47.056
It's like he's in a cult.

27:47.100 --> 27:48.318
- Okay.

27:48.362 --> 27:51.974
When did--when did
he meet Dr. Adler?

27:52.018 --> 27:56.022
- Um, freshman year
after he moved here,

27:56.065 --> 27:57.937
about six years ago.

27:57.980 --> 28:01.592
- At first, he used to call us
all the time.

28:01.636 --> 28:05.118
Now not even on holidays.

28:05.161 --> 28:08.991
- Did you--did you ever
try to bring him back?

28:09.035 --> 28:12.255
- We had an intervention.
We brought in our minister.

28:12.299 --> 28:17.173
I-I-I emptied
my retirement fund

28:17.217 --> 28:18.566
just to pay for a deprogrammer,

28:18.609 --> 28:22.004
but nothing worked.

28:22.048 --> 28:26.139
All we wanted
was to protect him.

28:27.706 --> 28:30.186
[solemn music]

28:30.230 --> 28:34.103
You... try to do

28:34.147 --> 28:36.366
everything right.

28:36.410 --> 28:38.020
♪

28:38.064 --> 28:41.328
But I don't know if my son
will ever come back.

28:41.371 --> 28:44.244
♪

28:44.287 --> 28:47.377
- These kids come from,
uh, abusive homes,

28:47.421 --> 28:48.727
repressive schools.

28:48.770 --> 28:51.425
They arrive, uh,
totally disconnected,

28:51.468 --> 28:52.513
unable to feel.

28:52.556 --> 28:54.123
- I get all that,

28:54.167 --> 28:55.908
but how do you go from there
to gang rape?

28:55.951 --> 28:57.692
- Rape? This is--
no, no.

28:57.736 --> 29:00.608
This is about cutting
through their armor,

29:00.651 --> 29:02.305
freeing their libido.

29:02.349 --> 29:05.221
Look, I-I-I'm not angry
at you, Amanda,

29:05.265 --> 29:08.094
for pretending
to be interested in my work.

29:08.137 --> 29:11.053
That ruse was--
that was your job.

29:11.097 --> 29:13.708
But did you actually read
anything I wrote?

29:13.752 --> 29:15.449
- Yeah, I read
every single one of your books.

29:15.492 --> 29:18.757
- Then why are you asking
the wrong questions?

29:18.800 --> 29:20.759
What fear is blocking you

29:20.802 --> 29:23.413
from feeling what I know
is inside you?

29:23.457 --> 29:24.980
- Don't do that, Doctor,

29:25.024 --> 29:27.026
'cause I am the only friend
you have in here.

29:27.069 --> 29:29.463
- Friend?

29:29.506 --> 29:31.508
I am offering you the chance

29:31.552 --> 29:33.772
to journey to dimensions

29:33.815 --> 29:35.382
you can't imagine,

29:35.425 --> 29:38.472
and your reaction is to play
the "good cop" card?

29:38.515 --> 29:41.431
I am so disappointed.

29:41.475 --> 29:43.085
- Hmm.
- Really.

29:43.129 --> 29:45.218
♪

29:45.261 --> 29:49.352
I would like to leave unless
I'm being charged with a crime.

29:49.396 --> 29:51.006
- Yes, actually.

29:51.050 --> 29:52.268
Possession, for now.

29:52.312 --> 29:54.401
- Well, that won't stand.

29:54.444 --> 29:56.272
I have
a government-approved grant

29:56.316 --> 29:58.535
for research into DMT.

29:58.579 --> 30:03.236
My institute is a de facto
extension of the university.

30:03.279 --> 30:06.630
But if the Great Purge
must proceed,

30:06.674 --> 30:09.459
then proceed it must.

30:09.503 --> 30:15.117
♪

30:15.161 --> 30:17.816
- So Adler's a false prophet.

30:17.859 --> 30:19.382
To paraphrase Joseph Campbell,

30:19.426 --> 30:21.080
the mystic swims
in the same water

30:21.123 --> 30:22.211
in which the psychotic drowns.

30:22.255 --> 30:23.691
- Even so, his students,

30:23.734 --> 30:25.171
still believe
everything he feeds them.

30:25.214 --> 30:26.650
- And the daughter
thinks he's a saint.

30:26.694 --> 30:28.087
The mother died
when she was three,

30:28.130 --> 30:29.653
so he raised her.

30:29.697 --> 30:33.048
- Something happened to Adler.

30:33.092 --> 30:34.354
Twenty years ago,

30:34.397 --> 30:36.008
he was one of
the foremost authorities

30:36.051 --> 30:37.574
in liberation psychiatry.

30:37.618 --> 30:40.012
- Okay, well, whatever
alternate reality he's in,

30:40.055 --> 30:42.101
this reality, he's guilty
of either conspiracy to rape

30:42.144 --> 30:43.276
or sex trafficking.

30:43.319 --> 30:45.147
- I agree.
Charge him with both.

30:45.191 --> 30:46.757
- How? Who am I
gonna put on the stand?

30:46.801 --> 30:48.847
Caleb?
Meghan and her elves?

30:48.890 --> 30:51.110
- Charge Anais.
Flip her.

30:51.153 --> 30:53.329
- She won't turn on him.
They're sutured.

30:53.373 --> 30:57.507
- Or maybe that's just another
alternate reality he's created.

30:57.551 --> 30:59.509
I found a marriage certificate.

30:59.553 --> 31:01.772
Adler married Kathleen Bell
in '94,

31:01.816 --> 31:05.298
but no obituary,
no death certificate.

31:05.341 --> 31:07.648
♪

31:07.691 --> 31:10.651
- Well, if she's
not deceased...

31:10.694 --> 31:13.306
then where is she?

31:13.349 --> 31:14.568
- Find out.

31:16.700 --> 31:19.703
♪

31:24.883 --> 31:25.013
.

31:25.057 --> 31:27.929
- Kathleen Bell Adler.
Admitted in '97.

31:27.973 --> 31:29.888
She was a brilliant clinician
until she was found naked

31:29.931 --> 31:31.019
in the middle
of Harvard Square.

31:31.063 --> 31:32.673
- What was her diagnosis?

31:32.716 --> 31:35.023
- Hallucinogenic-induced
psychosis

31:35.067 --> 31:36.895
with underlying
paranoid schizophrenia.

31:36.938 --> 31:38.940
- Can she communicate?
- Intermittently.

31:38.984 --> 31:41.595
This week, she's been having
agitated conversations

31:41.638 --> 31:44.511
with someone who's not there,
about her daughter.

31:44.554 --> 31:46.948
- Her daughter doesn't know
that her mother is even alive.

31:46.992 --> 31:50.909
- Anais?
Kathleen's worried about her.

31:50.952 --> 31:52.736
- Does her husband,
Dr. Adler, visit?

31:52.780 --> 31:54.913
- No one's ever visited her.
- Ever?

31:54.956 --> 31:56.479
- At least not since
I've been on staff.

31:56.523 --> 31:58.046
That's going on 15 years now.

31:58.090 --> 31:59.613
[forlorn music]

31:59.656 --> 32:01.528
- What's her prognosis?

32:01.571 --> 32:03.486
- After all this time here?

32:03.530 --> 32:05.575
No one reintegrates from that.

32:05.619 --> 32:07.969
♪

32:08.013 --> 32:09.579
- Thank you, Doctor.

32:11.712 --> 32:13.670
- Adler did this to her.

32:13.714 --> 32:15.759
- We don't know that.
- I do.

32:17.587 --> 32:19.502
Hey, Rollins, I know
that you have a blind spot

32:19.546 --> 32:21.504
for men that you think
are smarter than you--

32:21.548 --> 32:23.463
- No, I just want to ask him
about his wife.

32:23.506 --> 32:26.596
- Can I--can I actually
trust you with him?

32:26.640 --> 32:28.033
- Who else
is gonna get through?

32:28.076 --> 32:29.686
I mean, you, Fin, Carisi?
Okay, he thinks--

32:29.730 --> 32:32.037
he thinks you're all
so covered in armor,

32:32.080 --> 32:35.040
that you'll never open up.

32:35.083 --> 32:37.868
No offense.

32:37.912 --> 32:39.827
♪

32:39.870 --> 32:41.916
- [sighs]

32:45.528 --> 32:46.877
- Oh.

32:46.921 --> 32:51.839
So by, uh, altering
my external reality,

32:51.882 --> 32:54.189
you think you'll alter
my responses.

32:54.233 --> 32:55.669
Is that it?

32:55.712 --> 32:58.063
- I want to ask you
about your wife.

32:58.106 --> 32:59.760
- My wife?

33:01.588 --> 33:02.545
She's gone.

33:02.589 --> 33:04.504
- Gone, but not dead.

33:04.547 --> 33:07.420
- I'd ask you to, uh,
leave my wife alone.

33:07.463 --> 33:09.900
- Like you have?
- [sighs]

33:09.944 --> 33:14.818
Okay, time... in this world,
in this plane,

33:14.862 --> 33:16.820
has stopped for her.

33:16.864 --> 33:18.561
She's well taken care of,

33:18.605 --> 33:21.216
but the, uh, the kind of break
that she suffered,

33:21.260 --> 33:24.176
there's--there's no return.

33:24.219 --> 33:26.700
- The journeys you took her on,
she can't get back.

33:26.743 --> 33:28.615
- That was not the cause.

33:28.658 --> 33:32.749
Kathleen battled demons
her whole life.

33:32.793 --> 33:35.578
Her parents treated their dogs
better than they treated her.

33:35.622 --> 33:36.927
- How?

33:36.971 --> 33:38.929
'Cause she was
a-a well-regarded doctor--

33:38.973 --> 33:41.889
- No, no.
Not my fault.

33:41.932 --> 33:44.935
Her father raped her
when she was a child.

33:44.979 --> 33:48.200
She completely dissociated
from herself to survive.

33:48.243 --> 33:50.680
By the time she came to me,
she'd already seen,

33:50.724 --> 33:52.987
and been failed by,
a dozen therapists.

33:53.031 --> 33:54.771
- So you were her doctor.

33:54.815 --> 33:57.644
- Initially, yes,
for a psych evaluation.

33:57.687 --> 34:00.473
After a suicide attempt.
- And you slept with her?

34:01.648 --> 34:02.953
- Later.

34:02.997 --> 34:04.868
Yes, after I'd begun
treating her.

34:04.912 --> 34:06.261
- With the hallucinogens?

34:06.305 --> 34:08.829
- And love.

34:08.872 --> 34:10.961
And positive sexual energy.

34:11.005 --> 34:14.095
She was so depersonalized,
so derealized,

34:14.139 --> 34:15.662
the only way to heal her wounds

34:15.705 --> 34:17.838
was to go back to their cause

34:17.881 --> 34:20.232
and reprogram her response.

34:20.275 --> 34:21.798
- Reenacting?

34:21.842 --> 34:23.235
- Yes.

34:23.278 --> 34:25.498
And I can tell you,
it did work for a time.

34:25.541 --> 34:28.153
We were happy.
We conceived a child.

34:28.196 --> 34:31.852
But as Anais grew,
Kathleen flooded with memories.

34:31.895 --> 34:33.158
The abuse had started earlier

34:33.201 --> 34:34.985
than she'd let herself
remember.

34:35.029 --> 34:36.552
I did everything I could.

34:36.596 --> 34:38.946
- But you lost her.

34:38.989 --> 34:40.121
- Yes.

34:40.165 --> 34:43.081
And since then, I have...

34:43.124 --> 34:46.954
dedicated my life
to saving other victims.

34:46.997 --> 34:49.609
- That's...

34:49.652 --> 34:52.655
that's what I want
to hear about.

34:52.699 --> 34:55.136
- Oh, so many of them.

34:55.180 --> 34:59.575
It's more common
than you realize.

34:59.619 --> 35:01.577
Freud knew it
early on in his work.

35:01.621 --> 35:03.188
He--he...

35:03.231 --> 35:07.844
he saw how pervasive
child sex assault was,

35:07.888 --> 35:11.935
but academia wouldn't
even discuss incest.

35:11.979 --> 35:15.852
So he categorized their
memories as childhood fantasy.

35:15.896 --> 35:17.985
- The Oedipus complex.
- Yes.

35:18.028 --> 35:21.293
The original sin
of psychotherapy.

35:21.336 --> 35:23.121
- So these students
aren't drugging

35:23.164 --> 35:24.731
and assaulting these women,

35:24.774 --> 35:27.255
it's... therapy.

35:30.737 --> 35:32.652
- These young people
are drawn to us.

35:32.695 --> 35:34.741
They--they have deep wounds.

35:34.784 --> 35:37.047
Now, by--by altering

35:37.091 --> 35:39.180
their perception of reality,

35:39.224 --> 35:41.182
while reenacting their abuse,

35:41.226 --> 35:45.055
I am able to reconnect them
with their true selves.

35:45.099 --> 35:46.666
- True selves?

35:46.709 --> 35:48.189
Did that help the woman in--
in Bellevue?

35:48.233 --> 35:49.973
Because she may
never come back.

35:50.017 --> 35:52.062
Just like your wife,
who may never--

35:52.106 --> 35:54.195
- No! Not my fault!
Not my fault!

35:54.239 --> 35:56.719
They are--they are broken.

35:56.763 --> 35:58.112
I-I try to save them.

35:58.156 --> 35:59.374
You know this, Kathleen.

35:59.418 --> 36:01.159
- I...

36:02.943 --> 36:07.208
♪

36:07.252 --> 36:11.081
- Okay, all right, they have
sent you to silence me, okay?

36:11.125 --> 36:13.649
- That's not what's going on
here, Doctor.

36:13.693 --> 36:16.304
♪

36:16.348 --> 36:17.740
[sighs]

36:17.784 --> 36:20.874
You--you were brilliant.

36:20.917 --> 36:22.702
And look what's happened
to your mind.

36:22.745 --> 36:24.965
- My mind has evolved.

36:25.008 --> 36:26.923
That is why people
are so threatened by me.

36:26.967 --> 36:28.229
Who is out there?

36:28.273 --> 36:31.145
The AMA?
American Psychiatric?

36:31.189 --> 36:34.844
How many forces
conspire against me?

36:34.888 --> 36:36.106
Big Pharma?
You said yourself.

36:36.150 --> 36:37.282
They're only interested
in drugs

36:37.325 --> 36:39.153
in order to numb the soul.

36:39.197 --> 36:41.242
Who is out there?

36:41.286 --> 36:43.940
♪

36:43.984 --> 36:46.856
-No one's behind that glass
but my captain.

36:46.900 --> 36:50.077
- "Oh Captain, my Captain.

36:50.120 --> 36:51.992
"Our fearful trip is done.

36:52.035 --> 36:53.950
"The ship has weather'd
every rack,

36:53.994 --> 36:55.648
the prize we sought is won."

36:55.691 --> 36:58.259
- Dr. Adler, come back.
Stay with me.

36:58.303 --> 36:59.782
- No, no, no, no.

36:59.826 --> 37:01.654
That is the last thing
I will do.

37:01.697 --> 37:03.743
I will not sit there with you
and eat green eggs and ham.

37:03.786 --> 37:05.875
I will not give
a false confession.

37:05.919 --> 37:07.312
I will not be complicit

37:07.355 --> 37:10.750
in our society's bloodlust
for scapegoats!

37:10.793 --> 37:12.273
- Dr. Adler,
you can't go out that way.

37:12.317 --> 37:13.796
You can't go out that way.
- Too late.

37:13.840 --> 37:15.407
Going, going, gone!

37:15.450 --> 37:17.278
- Calm down.
- Gone! Gone!

37:17.322 --> 37:18.323
- Come down.

37:18.366 --> 37:19.933
Slow down.

37:19.976 --> 37:21.282
Calm down.
- Gone! Gone!

37:21.326 --> 37:23.197
- Come back here.
It's okay.

37:23.241 --> 37:25.982
Come, come, come.

37:26.026 --> 37:26.983
Come.

37:27.027 --> 37:29.812
- [gasps]
There she is!

37:29.856 --> 37:32.902
Oh, my beautiful bride!

37:32.946 --> 37:34.817
Oh, Kathleen!
Kathleen!

37:34.861 --> 37:36.428
- It's okay.

37:36.471 --> 37:39.039
- Oh, my beautiful bride.
My beautiful bride.

37:39.082 --> 37:42.390
Kathleen, how was your day?

37:42.434 --> 37:45.132
Tell me about your day, please.

37:45.175 --> 37:47.743
May I sit with you?

37:47.787 --> 37:49.223
Please, just for a moment.

37:49.267 --> 37:52.879
It's just us now.
Just us.

37:52.922 --> 37:57.318
[sobbing]

37:57.362 --> 38:00.016
- I've got an ambulance
on the way.

38:00.060 --> 38:02.192
- Could this be
an elaborate act?

38:02.236 --> 38:04.804
- If you ask me,
he's just escaped.

38:07.241 --> 38:08.895
[sighs]

38:15.118 --> 38:16.337
- There you are.

38:16.381 --> 38:18.513
- Hey, what's up?

38:18.557 --> 38:20.341
- Um, I went
and checked on Adler.

38:20.385 --> 38:22.082
He's been at Bellevue
for the last three days

38:22.125 --> 38:25.433
and hasn't eaten,
spoken, slept.

38:25.477 --> 38:28.393
He's completely unresponsive.
It's not a ruse.

38:28.436 --> 38:30.308
- Well, even so,
I still plan on arraigning him

38:30.351 --> 38:32.484
and his disciples,
including Anais.

38:32.527 --> 38:35.313
What they did to those women--
- I hear you.

38:35.356 --> 38:39.926
Just, can you give me 24 hours
before you arraign Anais?

38:39.969 --> 38:41.884
- Yeah.
Yeah, sure.

38:41.928 --> 38:43.321
- Thanks.

38:43.364 --> 38:47.063
- Hey, Rollins,
if you don't mind me asking.

38:47.107 --> 38:49.457
What's your deal with this guy?

38:49.501 --> 38:53.331
- I wanted to hear
his side of the story.

38:53.374 --> 38:56.421
I had no idea
how far gone he was.

38:59.249 --> 39:03.079
There was a time that...

39:03.123 --> 39:05.125
I was lost and...

39:07.562 --> 39:09.825
thought he had the answers,
I wanted to learn from him.

39:09.869 --> 39:13.002
I wanted to follow him.

39:13.046 --> 39:14.482
- Yeah, but you didn't.

39:14.526 --> 39:16.397
You were smart, Rollins.

39:16.441 --> 39:19.835
- Hmm.
- Hey.

39:19.879 --> 39:21.924
You dodged a bullet.

39:21.968 --> 39:23.317
- Yeah.

39:25.275 --> 39:28.235
[solemn music]

39:28.278 --> 39:32.152
♪

39:36.504 --> 39:38.419
- Will she know who I am?

39:38.463 --> 39:40.247
- She's been here 20 years.

39:40.290 --> 39:41.901
You can't expect too much.

39:41.944 --> 39:43.424
- I didn't even know
she was alive.

39:43.468 --> 39:45.165
- The doctor understands.

39:45.208 --> 39:46.862
- If you're not up for this,

39:46.906 --> 39:48.603
we can turn around right now.

39:48.647 --> 39:50.475
- She's my mother.

39:52.477 --> 39:57.090
♪

39:57.133 --> 39:58.483
- Kathleen?

40:01.181 --> 40:04.576
- Mom?
It's me.

40:04.619 --> 40:07.317
Anais.

40:07.361 --> 40:10.233
- Yes.

40:10.277 --> 40:12.366
- Do you mind if I sit?

40:14.977 --> 40:19.982
♪

40:22.594 --> 40:24.900
- Are you okay?

40:26.032 --> 40:28.991
♪

40:29.035 --> 40:32.342
- Am I?

40:32.386 --> 40:34.170
I don't know.

40:36.651 --> 40:41.526
- Your father and I
were just talking about you.

40:43.919 --> 40:50.926
♪

40:57.324 --> 41:04.331
♪

41:14.341 --> 41:14.515
.

41:14.559 --> 41:17.475
[dramatic music]

41:17.518 --> 41:24.482
♪

41:43.283 --> 41:46.286
[wolf howls]
